THE father who allegedly incidentally shot his teenage son dead, broke down in court and his wife comforted him on Thursday. Emanuel Tshabalala shot his son outside his school in Ennerdale, south of Joburg on Tuesday evening. He was released on bail as the state did not oppose bail. Tshabalala handed himself to the police after the incident and was charged with the murder of his 14-year-old son. According to the police the man allegedly took his son to school to attend evening classes. He dropped the boy off at the school and he locked his vehicle and waited inside. Following that, he fell asleep in the car, the boy later on came back and knocked on the passenger window of his father's vehicle. "The father who was asleep in the car with his firearm on him... got scared by the knocking of his son[and] he pulled out his firearm and shot towards the direction of the person who was knocking," said Soweto West cluster spokesperson Captain Mpande Khoza. The father then realised that he had shot his son. The teenager died on his to the hospital.   